properties.description:
Optional dictionary of user defined formats, as explained here:
http://formatjs.io/guides/message-syntax/#custom-formats

For example, a valid dictionary of formats would be:
this.formats = {
   number: { USD: { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' } }
}

methods.description:
Fires a page change request event

Only called if remoteData==true

Information is stored in `evt.detail`:
```
document.getElementById("mytable").addEventListener("px-page-change-intent", function(e) {
  var data = e.detail;
  console.log("Intended page: ", data);
});
```

